cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the semantics of Prolog, which is a programming language used in artificial intelligence and computational logic. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the Byrd box model, which is a technique used in logic programming and automated reasoning, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) another likely category. The paper also discusses the implementation of Prolog tracers, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also touches upon the limitations of the Prolog resolution box model, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
